03/06/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal announced Friday (June 1st) that it will launch a probe into the circumstances under which Croatian Television (HTV) published parts of a classified ICTY document. 
In its prime time news broadcast on May 28th, HTV broadcast parts of a classified annex to the indictment of three former Croatian generals, Ante Gotovina, Mladen Markac and Ivan Cermak. 
Seven other Croatian nationals were named in the annex. 
(Hina, HRT, B 92 - 01/06/07)
